reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Translation, Weird On Some Names
reviews.reviewText: All-around great translation of yet another one of Maruyama's PEAK Overlord LN volumes. My only real nitpick is that some of the names like Bukubukuchagama are rather confusingly (for fans of the series like me at least already familiar with their Japanese names) translated into English. The first time I read "BubblingTeapot" I was confused but figured out who it was by a bit of googling and some context clues. Not really much else to say other than that So-Bin and Maruyama outdid themselves once again with the art and writing respectively.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Major cliff hanger ahead
reviews.reviewText: I only give 4 out of 5 to an author that consistently pumps out 5 star LNs because of pacing. The book was an entertaining read but did little in the way of world building, and unfortunately, the story pacing fell flat on its face here. There were less than 20 pages that truly moved the plot along it felt like. Volume 15 was fluff along with lore and character building, but volume 16 was mostly an add to that fluff, like perhaps 90% to 95% fluff. That being said, with only 2 more volumes to go, perhaps the next two will somehow build off this one in unquie ways that makes the filler an important linchpin. Without giving spoilers, there wasn't too much open ended points for offshoots, nor new jumping points, with the end of the first chapter being a story enchantment possibility, and the end of the second chapter which answers an important question Ainz had, while progressing the story to the end.I know light novels should be light with the standard 200 page range, but these volumes would have been better as a side story release and combined for a full book.I don't regret binge reading this volume at all, but I do wish there had been more to it.5 stars to the author though who is writing this series as a passionate hobby, and has a different full-time day job that isn't writing (or authoring related at all I believe I read somewhere but don't quote me on that).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Overlord series is in my opinion one of the best light novels out there, cool story, interesting characters, overpowered main character (although sometimes the misunderstanding levels are going too far), i like it, so high rating, BUT, i feel like author kinda ran out of ideas after Holy Kingdom arc. The story is almost done, and yet reading tome 15&16 feel like we are in middle of it, not the end. Plus they are very lacking in terms of pushing the story forward.

reviews.reviewTitle: Less book for a higher price
reviews.reviewText: Welp at least the story feels back on track but about 100 pages less for a higher price is milking it.

Dayum I waited for years for this volume to finally be released and it was worth every second.I couldn't stop reading once I started and could only hope it wouldn't end. I still have no idea how Maruyama is going to end the story in just 2 other volumes, and it saddens me that the journey we experienced in one of the worlds with the best world building is coming to an end... 10/10
